depends_on tells Terraform — "create this resource ONLY AFTER that resource is ready"

depends_on explicitly tells Terraform to create a resource only after specified resources are ready. 
It is needed when the dependency is not a direct reference — like IAM policy attachments that must exist before EKS cluster creation. ✅

Example — without depends_on (problem):

# Terraform may create both at same time ❌
resource "aws_instance" "web" {
  ami           = "ami-12345"
  instance_type = "t3.micro"
  subnet_id     = aws_subnet.main.id
}

resource "aws_subnet" "main" {
  vpc_id     = aws_vpc.main.id
  cidr_block = "10.0.1.0/24"
}
# EC2 may try to create before subnet is ready ❌

Example — with depends_on (solution):

resource "aws_instance" "web" {
  ami           = "ami-12345"
  instance_type = "t3.micro"
  subnet_id     = aws_subnet.main.id

  depends_on = [aws_subnet.main]  # wait for subnet first ✅
}

resource "aws_subnet" "main" {
  vpc_id     = aws_vpc.main.id
  cidr_block = "10.0.1.0/24"
}

